description:
In scanner.rs SaplingIvkDecryptor::try_decrypt_sapling (line 211):

  let fr: jubjub::Fr = jubjub::Fr::from_repr(*self.ivk_bytes)
      .into_option()
      .expect("...");
  let ivk = SaplingIvk(fr);
  let prepared_ivk = PreparedIncomingViewingKey::new(&ivk);

This re-derives jubjub::Fr and reconstructs PreparedIncomingViewingKey on EVERY call to try_decrypt_sapling -- once per Sapling output per transaction per block.

PreparedIncomingViewingKey::new() involves a Jubjub scalar multiplication to precompute the Zcash trial-decryption tables. This is designed to be computed once per IVK and reused across many outputs. The ZF lightwalletd client library caches it for exactly this reason.

On mainnet, a single block can contain hundreds of Sapling outputs. For each output, the scanner reconstructs Fr from bytes (field deserialization), wraps it in SaplingIvk, and recomputes PreparedIncomingViewingKey. This is O(outputs_per_block) scalar multiplications when it should be O(1) per scanner session.

Fix: store PreparedIncomingViewingKey in SaplingIvkDecryptor at construction time rather than reconstructing it on each call. The struct already notes this pattern in its comment but does not implement it.
